[10:59.55]LAERTES Must there no more be done?
[11:01.54]First Priest No more be done:
[11:02.78] We should profane the service of the dead
[11:05.51] To sing a requiem and such rest to her
[11:08.80] As to peace-parted souls.
[11:10.36]LAERTES Lay her i' the earth:
[11:11.60] And from her fair and unpolluted flesh
[11:16.13] May violets spring! I tell thee, churlish priest,
