[13:14.32] I'll do't. Dost thou come here to whine?
[13:17.24] To outface me with leaping in her grave?
[13:20.90] Be buried quick with her, and so will I:
[13:23.58] And, if thou prate of mountains, let them throw
[13:25.88] Millions of acres on us, till our ground,
[13:27.99] Singeing his pate against the burning zone,
[13:30.41] Make Ossa like a wart! Nay, an thou'lt mouth,
